Interface IComponentNameProvider

    public interface IComponentNameProvider
    Provides a human-readable label for a terminology component.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static IComponentNameProvider NOOP_NAME_PROVIDER
      No-operation name provider that always behaves as String.valueOf(Object) for any input.

    • Field Detail

      • NOOP_NAME_PROVIDER

        static final IComponentNameProvider NOOP_NAME_PROVIDER
        No-operation name provider that always behaves as String.valueOf(Object) for any input.

    • Method Detail

      • getComponentLabel

        String getComponentLabel(IBranchPath branchPath,
                         String componentId)
        Returns with the human readable label of a terminology independent component identified by its unique ID from the given branch. This method may return with null if the component cannot be found on the specified branch with the given component ID.
        Parameters:
        branchPath - the branch path uniquely identifying the branch where the lookup has to be performed.
        componentId - the terminology specific unique ID of the component.
        Returns:
        the name/label of the component. Or null if the component cannot be found.
